name: Yakima County Health District COVID Vaccination Site
address: S 16th Ave & West Nob Hill Boulevard, Yakima WA, 98902
info: ***1ST & 2nd DOSE PFIZER VACCINATIONS***!!!!VACUNAS DE PRIMERA Y SECUNDA DOSIS DE PFIZER!!!! The vaccination clinic will take place at Yakima Valley College. Enter the YVC campus at the intersection between S 16th Ave and Arlington St. Continue on Arlington St and turn right onto S 12th Ave. The vaccination site will be at the parking lot next to the baseball field and bookstore. Masks are required. Please wear clothing which allows access to your shoulder. Vaccinations at this site are reserved for people who live and/or work in Washington State. All individuals 12 and over are eligible to get vaccinated. Those under 18 must be accompanied by a parent/guardian or must get parental consent via video/phone call or paper format. La clínica de vacunación se ubicara en Yakima Valley College. Ingrese al campus de YVC en la intersección entre S 16th Ave y Arlington St. Continue en Arlington St y gire a la derecha en S 12th Ave. El sitio de vacunación estará en el estacionamiento junto al campo de beisbol y la librería. Se requieren máscaras. Por favor, use ropa que permita acceso a su brazo. Las vacunas en este sitio están reservadas para las personas que viven o trabajan en el estado de Washington. Todas las personas mayores de 12 años son elegibles para vacunarse. Los menores de 18 años deben estar acompañados por un padre/tutor o deben obtener el consentimiento de los padres por video/llamada telefónica o en papel. ***1ST AND 2nd DOSE PFIZER VACCINATIONS***!!!!VACUNAS DE PRIMERA Y SEGUNDA DOSIS DE PFIZER!!!!
special: If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.

name: Consistent Care Services- COVID Vaccine Site
address: 1235 North Post St. Suite 201, Spokane WA, 99205
vaccines: Janssen COVID-19 Vaccine, Pfizer-BioNTech COVID-19 Vaccine
info:
***This is a clinic for 1st or 2nd doses of the Pfizer COVID-19 vaccine OR the single dose of Johnson & Johnson. *** All patients 12 years old and older can register for the Pfizer vaccine you must be 18 or older for the Johnson & Johnson vaccine. (If 12-17 years old for the Pfizer vaccine, you must be with a parent or guardian or have parental/guardian consent) Vaccinations at the Consistent Care Services COVID Vaccine Clinic are by appointment only. The clinic is located at 1235 N. Post St., Spokane WA 99201. The clinic is located upstairs in suite 201. There is elevator access or stairs. Enter the building at the time of your appointment only.

***Please no outside food or drinks***  
*VERY IMPORTANT*
***Please complete all the insurance/Medicare/Medicaid information when registering online for your appointment to avoid filling it out at the clinic***

name: Adna Fire Dept Clinic
info: ****This is a JOHNSON & JOHNSON single dose clinic**** and is by appointment or walk in. Please note: Johnson & Johnson vaccine can only be administered to individuals 18 years of age or older according CDC requirements.  This clinic is located at and hosted by Lewis County Fire District 6 at Adna Fire Station in partnership with Lewis County Public Health and Social Services, WA Department of Health and WA National Guard. This is a walk-up location. Please let us know if you or someone you are accompanying needs assistance of any kind. **You should also plan your visit around waiting for 15 minutes in the observation area so we can monitor for any unlikely adverse reactions to the vaccine.** Certain people with pre-identified conditions or past anaphylaxis events may be asked to wait for 30 minutes of observation. Free language translation services are provided. Video ASL translation is also provided. Please do not come if you are feeling ill. It is best to wear clothes that will allow for access to your upper arm, just below the shoulder. **Masks are required. If you do not have a mask, one will be provided.
special: If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.

name: Rebel Med NW - COVID Vaccine Clinic
address: 5401 Leary Ave NW STE 202, Seattle WA, 98107
info: ***We will accept both first and second dose appointments***  Insured, medicaid, medicare, and uninsured options all available. Walk-in's welcome, but will be advised to fill out information via this same sign up via kiosk. We are administering the first/second dose of the Moderna vaccine. Moderna is currently approved for all adults 18 years and older. Please bring a face covering that covers the mouth and nose. Everyone is required to stay 15-30 minutes under observation after receiving the vaccine. ****Rebel Med NW is located on the 2nd floor, with the entrance on NW Vernon Place above the nail salon. Across the street from the Olympic Athletic Club. ~~~We are an integrative medical clinic specializing in Naturopathic Primary Care, Acupuncture, and Mind Body Medicine.~~~ Please be respectful of the space as treatments may be ongoing. Please contact 206-297-6013, and ask to speak to a provider on call if you have a question, leave a voicemail and we will return as soon as we are available. Call 911 if life-threatening emergency, and you are in need of immediate help.

name: Onestop Medical Clinic - Covid Vaccination Venue
info:
• Onestop Medical, a Primary Care Clinic is serving the community by administering COVID-19 vaccines as a giving back in the current difficult situation since January 2021. Please DO NOT disrespect our hardworking staff and volunteers. No profanity please.
	
	• We are administering Pfizer COVID-19 vaccines to the patients age 12 years and above.
	
	• Due to the social distancing limitations and limited parking, please plan to arrive NO earlier than 5 Minutes. Please DO NOT park in front of our neighbor’s building; 1316 Central Ave S. The extra public parking is available next door at the Kent Municipal Court (1220 Central Ave S, Kent, WA 98032).
	
	• We ask that for everyone’s safety, please DO NOT visit this vaccination drive without an appointment. Please DO NOT email or call us to inquire, schedule, reschedule, cancel your appointment about COVID-19 Vaccine as we are experiencing extremely high email and call volumes. Please DO NOT book an appointment from the Zocodoc or Onestop Medical's website for COVID-19 Immunization.
	
	• Please schedule your Dose 2 through Prepmod.doh.wa.gov between 21 to 42 (at least 17 days considering grace period) days apart. Please DO NOT laminate the vaccine card. 
 
	• Please remember that you will need to bring your photo ID/Passport, medical insurance card (if insured). If you're receiving your 2nd vaccination, you will be required to bring your vaccination card too.

	• We DO NOT accept any form of payment, donation for COVID-19 vaccine from any patient. Please DO NOT make any payment to the Onestop Medical. If you receive a bill for your COVID vaccine, please contact your insurance company First.
	If you DO NOT have an insurance, no worries and you will still receive your vaccine.
	If you have Insurance a small Admin Fee will be charged to the insurance. The patient DOES NOT PAY for any vaccine related services out-of-pocket  The Admin Fee will be used to help cover a portion of the cost to maintain the staff, PPEs and all medical need.
	
	https://www.doh.wa.gov/Emergencies/COVID19/VaccineInformation/VaccineCost#heading67668
